trend_summary: Across the series, forested land is steadily converted to housing and civic uses. Cul-de-sac suburbs proliferate along the north–south corridor, while an oval stadium and a large central excavation emerge mid-period. Road capacity rises but high-rise footprints stay absent, so tree cover remains patchy. Built-up area grows roughly one-quarter, yielding a distinctly suburban, medium-density landscape.
notable_changes: Oval athletics stadium constructed on the northern plateau between early and mid images.
Large central clearing/quarry appears, expanding through mid-series before stabilising.
Incremental residential infill edges existing cul-de-sac neighbourhoods, especially southeast.
North–south arterial road widened and new junctions added, improving connectivity.
Late-period images show modest canopy recovery on the southwest fringe, indicating greening or reclamation.
